rComments: Had an amazing time in the course. Straight-forward, clear, helps when you ask him. Course content was made logical and interesting. Never liked children until I took this course. I vibed with him every time I went to his office hours. Hard grader, tests and exam was dense and detail oriented. Worth the challenge.

Professor VanderLaan is honestly a pretty good teacher. His lectures are interesting and straightforward which I loved. Midterms are fair game. He focuses on lectures and the textbook. His practice tests are very useful too. If you stay focused, you'll ace it. Overall, cool prof to have!

Prof Vanderlaan is predictable. Study the book and listen in lecture. Somewhat approachable - I used to think he was a bit rude but he's just like that. I think he means well. He tells the class the exam essay question in advance which was really helpful

Good prof. Boringish style but that can be a good thing because he is predictable. Does enough things to help students do well like practice tests and being available for office hours. Just beware that for tests he wants you to stick to exactly what was discussed, no being creative and adding extra insight or going for style points.
Uses TopHat to mark attendance, but other than that, his lectures are verbatim from the textbook. Sometimes a little rude, but overall a good class. Very knowledgeable.

He is a very good proff. He gave practice tests, so we could prepare for the midterms, and some of the questions from his practice test actually came up in the midterm. Short answers are directly from his lecture slides and mc and t/f were both from the textbook and lecture slides. Will definitely be taking classes with him in the future!
Tests were difficult but fair, mostly based on lectures but definitely recommend reading the textbook as well. Does multiple choice, true/false and short answer.

Lectures can be interesting and you learn a lot of things you didn't know before. Grading is a bit tough so put a lot of effort into studying for tests and writing the papers. It's a writing-heavy course but the plus side is that that was no exam.

He was an associate professor when I had him, but he was great. Lectures were interesting,  and assignments were ideal in that they allowed you to apply what you've learnt. I loved the course and would love to take another course with him in the future.
